<b><it>I Was Lord Kitchener's Valet</it></b> was a clothing <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../636/2858636.xml">
boutique</link> which achieved a period of fame in 1960s <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../284/463284.xml">
Swinging London</link> by promoting antique military uniforms as fashion items.<p>

It was founded by Jimmy Connors, owned by Ian Fisk and run by Robert Orbach. The original store opened in 1964 at 293 Portobello Road in London's <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../200/94200.xml">
Notting Hill</link></site>
. Due to its great popularity throughout 1966 and 1967 new stores opened on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../235/417235.xml">
The Kings Road</link> and Carnaby Court off <artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<street wordnetid="104334599" confidence="0.8">
<way wordnetid="104564698" confidence="0.8">
<thoroughfare wordnetid="104426618" confidence="0.8">
<road wordnetid="104096066" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../221/429221.xml">
Carnaby Street</link></road>
</thoroughfare>
</way>
</street>
</artifact>
.</p>
